Another impeccable multi-pack box hit our pressroom floor last year for @theory11 - Lord of the Rings. This box is different from the Beatles Box Set we produced for Theory11 in that it holds 4 decks but with two decks stacked - making it appear as though there are just 3 decks. Additionally, the insert is made of foam instead of paper. And it has a small piece of ribbon on the middle deck to encourage the user to lift it, lifting the middle deck and revealing the 4th deck underneath. The foil, embossing and construction that went into this box speaks to our pressroom operators’ high level of skill and expertise. Will you be buying one?

Share this with someone that loves Lord of the Rings! 

//

Cosmic print release alert! 🌀 We're counting down the minutes to Wednesday's opening of Transdimensional Multiversal Nonlinear Cosmic Traveler, Michael Engebretson's upcoming solo exhibition at Interact Gallery! Coinciding with the show, we're excited to announce a new collaboration with @studioonfire, a best in class impression-based printing, luxury consumer packaging, and design studio based in St. Paul. In addition to a robust commercial program, Studio On Fire produces fine art impression-based prints for artists, designers, and musicians across the U.S. 
 
Studio On Fire is teaming up with artist and disability advocate Engebretson to publish a new limited edition letterpress print, just in time for the show. Titled “Class 5 Hyper Industrial Duty Distillation Station,” the two-color edition will be released at Engebretson's opening reception next week. 

THE DETAILS 

Opening Reception & Print Release 
Wednesday, March 1, 5-8 p.m. 
Free and open to the public 
Remarks & Artist reading at 6 p.m. 

Interact Gallery 
755 Prior Avenue North, Suite 002D (lower level), St. Paul, MN 55104 
(651) 756-1246 
Gallery.interactcenterarts.org 

The exhibition, “Transdimensional Multiversal Nonlinear Cosmic Traveler,” runs March 1-April 14, 2023. 

#MichaelEngebretson

Video & image descriptions: (1) Studio On Fire Press Operator Elyssa McCrae runs a print through the letterpress with Michael Engbretson. (2) Engebretson holds a complete print in the Interact studio. (3) A video of Engebretson making the original drawing for the print. (4) Engebretson's limited edition letterpress print, titled Class 5 Hyper Industrial Duty Distillation Station. A series of black geometric shapes form the outline of a spaceship. Yellow-green marks are added in a second layer, detailing different sectors of the ship.

Resource stewardship is one of Studio On Fire’s core values and we are always seeking environmentally sustainable solutions. Our uncoated papers, inks, and foils are recyclable and compostable. Many of the papers we use are made with a minimum of 30% recycled post consumer fibers and come from FSC (responsible forestry certified) manufacturers who use 100% renewable green electricity and process their materials chlorine free.

To celebrate Earth Day tomorrow, give a follow and support our friends @greatrivergreening. They're committed to conserving healthy, climate change-resilient ecosystems throughout Minnesota. Check out their page to learn more about the great work they do in our communities!

//

Did you catch our post a few weeks ago about @goodandwellsupplyco's latest candle collection? We designed and produced the boxes for their Wildflower candles.

The process started with our structural development team. They prototyped, tested, and designed the custom three-piece box that houses their unique candles and keep them safe. Next, our graphic design team worked with Good & Well Supply Co. to develop the illustrations and graphics that cover the surface each box. Our prepress and tooling specialists turned that artwork into plates and our production team letterpressed the box tops and bottoms, diecut all three parts of the boxes, and fold/glued them before sending them off to Good & Well to be filled with the candles.

We just published a case study on our website detailing this project - click the link in our bio to read more! Let us know in the comments which box is your favorite?

social_posts.post_text:
A few weeks ago, Studio One Fire got the chance to bring their tabletop press over to @interactcenterarts ! We all had a blast discussing art, seeing their studio, and printing fun coasters in celebration and recognition of Disability Pride Month. The coaster design was done by Interact artist Rosemary Perronteau. It was selected from multiple entries by Interact’s Artist Advisory Council, which is made up of performing and visual artists from within their organization.

Interact hosts a supportive creative space where artists with disabilities develop their professional studio and theater practices. They also have a gallery that gets their visual artists’ work in front of an eager audience. Over 100 artists currently call Interact their studio, participating in a variety of art-making (painting, drawing, theatre, and so much more).

Studio On Fire is both neighbor and friend of Interact. We specialize in impression-based printing methods like letterpress, foil-stamping, embossing, and more. And when possible, we try to engage with our local community and support the thriving art scene the Twin Cities has to offer.

Be sure to follow Interact to keep up to date on their latest events and shows, or browse their website for available art to purchase to continue supporting them!

//
